The extraordinary capability of metasurfaces to control light at nanoscale would also open potential disruptive developments in optical signal processing applications. As illustrated in Fig. 5h, coherently controlled absorption in a fully fiberized and packaged switching meta-device was recently reported96. An optical fiber meta-tip platform was conceived demonstrating logical functions (XOR, NOT and AND) at wavelengths between 1530 and 1565 nm. The proposed metadevice has been successfully tested at up to 40 gigabits per second, opening new opportunities for 100 THz bandwidth single-photon operation with potential impact in quantum information networks97,98. Meanwhile, fiber facet-integrated meta-structures are also exploited for structured light generations and beam shaping256–259. Figure 5i sketches the SEM images of the meta-facet fiber for generating OAM beam with topological charge ℓ=+1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
